I am a member of Shadows of Yamabushi, and am one of the main people saying here that the door DOES affect agro.  It has been my experience on more servers than just that rathe that this is true, and yes, I have done testing to support this, thus my above scenario.<br>
<br>
I agree with the opinions of most of the people who have posted between my last post and this one.  There is TOO MUCH of a coincidence with mobs agroing for &quot;no apparent reason&quot; when the door is opened.<br>
<br>
Oh and...Shadows of Yamabushi does not bring KoS people to our HoT farming sessions either.  We did once, learned from our mistake, and now bring only non-KoS people.  So that is not the issue.  The door opening is the ONLY variable, with the exception of possible shoddy programming of the walls as described above.  And even in this scenario, the hub mobs have only attacked us for &quot;no reason&quot; when the door was OPEN.<br>
<br>
Clearing up Kamlatir's post with his list of anti-asking guilds (Kenshiiro likes us to ask too, so for all intents and purposes, Yamabushi ASKS to open the door&gt; and reiterating his point,<br>
