<br>
When NB was still CoV alligned and doing Doze raids regularly, opening the door was a standard practice.  We did it all the time.  I'd open to the door and walk through it whenever it got a little hairy with AE adds in the caster camp.  In my experience every single time we have ever gotten trained we spammed in /gu &quot;WHO DRAGGED A CORPSE?&quot; and every single time someone piped up &quot;All I did was drag soandso's corpse man, it's not like it's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> my</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> fault we got trained&quot;.<br>
<br>
Point is, door opened, door closed, we never got trained unless someone dragged, someone KoS got too close, a mob got bashed too close to the door.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> There is TOO MUCH of a coincidence with mobs agroing for &quot;no apparent reason&quot; when the door is opened.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Of course there is.  NPC's will open unlocked doors to get through them.  Here's what happens: A hub mob gets aggro, for whatever reason.  Mob runs around in circles because of bad pathing around doors and firepots, chain-aggroing all of his friends.  Mob paths to door.  Mob opens door.  Guild_Leader00 shouts, &quot;WHO OPENED THE DOOR?  WE'RE GONNA GET TRAINED!&quot;  Mob chain aggro's all his friends, guild gets trained.  Guild_Leader00 shouts, &quot;SEE WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU OPEN THE DOOR?  DON'T OPEN IT!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> With the door closed you can fight mobs anywhere in HoT up to as close as about 3 feet from the door. This might vary with the type of mob.. but we have fought right up near the door many times without agro'ing the CoV dragons. The few times we did agro the CoV, it was when the mobs were believed to get too close to the door.<br>
<br>
With the door open, you can fight mobs anywhere in HoT up to about 10 feet (about halfway door-to-wall) from the door (yes, you can fight in los).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> That's funny, because we've occasionally had mobs positioned badly, and fought them *right in front of the door* such that their tails were sticking through the door and out the other side, with no aggro.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There are wanderers in the hub, who get much closer to the door than the two guards on the side. (have been kos to CoV for the past several months, memory is a bit shakey here.)  IIRC, there are 2 guards in the hub, facing towards the center.  There are about 4 mobs who wander, and get much closer to the door than anyone else does, and more importantly, when he's approaching the door, is facing it.  You can have a mob, as Rogg said, right up against the door when there's no wanderers nearby and you won't get aggro, independant of the door being open or closed. (the door being opened at this time probably <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> would</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cause aggro because the mob would likely be bashed through it and much closer to the static spawn guards)  However, a wanderer will eventually walk up 20-30 seconds later, be facing the door (increasing aggro range dramatically) chain aggro everything, open the door, and kill everyone, resulting in the guildleader the door open is the cause rather than the effect.<br>
<br>
Someone made the comment along the lines of &quot;Doors block AE- I was standing outside the door to Doze's room while we were fighting him and the AE didn't hit me&quot; (can't find it for the life of me)  FYI- the stairs you were standing on block AE too, especially because of how short Doze is.  LoS in EQ is funky as hell.  You can be standing right next to a mob, especially in the presence of lots of corners and firepots and not be hit with AE when you're in full sight of him.  You can be standing behind a corner and be hit by AE when none of the 10+ clerics standing next to you got hit. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
