<br>
Try some experiments to determine the validity of the statements above. Sure, noone wants an entire raid party to die, so try it with one group or so, move the raid party to the hub.<br>
<br>
We know that Dragro and KoS agro are obvious deaths, so let's rule these out of the equation at the beginning and concentrate on the other three possibilities of death, LoS, proximity, and AE agros. The one outstanding item that affects these MAY or MAY NOT BE, the DOOR. So let's test the DOOR. <br>
<br>
Control factors for both tests: Make sure noone on your party is KoS or drags a corpse. Also, until the AE test (2), try to do without bard songs, jic, though this is relatively superfluous.<br>
<br>
TEST 1: This test will show the effects of LoS agro and Proximity agro on a NON-AE mob. HYPOTHESIS: The door discourages LoS and proximity agro, therefore, keeping the door closed during a fight is necessary to prevent death.<br>
<br>
   Step1: DOOR CLOSED, Pull non-AE mob to the foyer in front <br>
             of the door, to about 3 feet from the door. <br>
         Do Static mobs agro? If No, go to step 2. <br>
               If Yes, CONCLUSION: Proximity to mobs caused <br>
               agro, opening the Door (LoS) has no affect.<br>
         Does roaming mob (Zemm) agro? If No, go to step 2.  <br>
             If Yes, CONCLUSION: Proximity to mobs caused <br>
             agro, opening the Door (LoS) has no affect.<br>
   Step2: While mob is being attacked, OPEN the door.<br>
         Do Static mobs agro? If No, CONCLUSION: opening the <br>
             door (LoS) and Proximity have no affect. <br>
             If Yes, CONCLUSION: opening the door DOES<br>
             create LoS agro, Proximity has no affect.<br>
         Does roaming mob (Zemm) agro? If No, CONCLUSION: <br>
             opening the door has no affect on LoS and/or Prox. <br>
             If Yes, CONCLUSION: opening the door does <br>
             allow LoS agro or Proximity agro to take affect.<br>
<br>
Test2: This test will show the effects of an AE casting NPC on agro. HYPOTHESIS: The Door discourages the affects of AE beyond it's edge. For this test, simply repeat the steps in Test1 with an AE mob. The same conclusions can be drawn for this test as in Test1 with regards to the results of AE's affects.<br>
    NOTE: This test may be unnecessary depending on the <br>
    outcome of Test1.<br>
<br>
Put up or shut up. Get some logs and post them. <br>
<br>
One thing needs to be stressed. People have requested that you ask before opening the door. It's not that hard to do and saves much aggravation and hatred from forming. <br>
<br>
Elder Essagare Eldertree<br>
Heirophant<br>
