in some ways may not be a &quot;bug&quot; per say just a fault of programming.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/u3vi1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>3vi1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/20/02 7:53:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   My 2cp</span><hr size=1> Hey guys,<br>
<br>
Unless they changed something, doors don't truly exist server-side.  Remember the old bug where you are running at a locked door, go LD, log back in and find yourself on the other side?  They may have added some code to fix this, but I don't think mobs can detect if a door is open, or even locked.<br>
<br>
Door state drawing is all done client side.  If a mob comes through a door, the client animates it opening if it's unlocked.  If it's locked, the client knows not to draw it opening.<br>
<br>
But, the mobs will still walk through it, because as the server 'sees' things it doesn't even exist.  We've pulled the Servitor through the locked door in Griegs with AE when whatshisface was bugged, so I'm 100% sure the server doesn't care about them.<br>
<br>
On a similar note, there appear to be certain walls that are server side only too.  I was running east, along the south wall, in UP and went LD.  Lo and behold my surprise to find myself in the tunnel to Vex Thal, beyond the locked door.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR><HR><IMG src="http://www.eternaldusk.com/images/imgKaotiqa.gif" border=0><BR>
